      "pulseWidth": {
        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "value": 50,
        "unit": "ns",
        "description": "Nanosecond regime (10-150 ns) typical for concrete to enable ablation with minimal heat-affected zone (HAZ); picosecond (ps) or femtosecond (fs) reduces HAZ further but increases cost. Recommended 50 ns for efficient contaminant removal without cracking porous concrete. Source: Laser physics research in Appl. Surf. Sci. (2019) on pulsed laser ablation of cementitious materials."
      },
